Requested Review: Slot Supervisor Kaitlyn Lewis contacted Surveillance for a review on NRT2 as an unknown female claimed that she put a $75 Tito ticket in NRT2 and it only dispensed 0.50 cents. Kaitlyn wished to confirm this. Footage confirmed the female inserted one TITO and SDS confirms that a $0.50 TITO was inserted at that time. Further review showed her playing several machines, but not cashing out any TITO; however at 1444hrs she can be seen inserting a TITO for $70 at NRT3 and collecting the funds. Kaitlyn was informed and spoke to the female. Kaitlyn stated the guest was satisfied with the result.

Requested Review: Casino Shift Manager Trevor Poole requested a review of the last spin on RL2 after a confusion between two players regarding who placed the winning column bet when 33B hit. Upon review, Surveillance observed an Unknown Male guest wearing a green hoodie placing the bet at 0023hrs. CSM Poole was notified of the findings.

Requested Review: CSM Blair Cameron requested a review of guests on spots 6 and 9, Poker 5, and advised surveillance that the two guests may have been passing chips. Upon review, surveillance observed the players at spot 6 and spot 9 passing chips to each other within the timeline provided by CSM Blair Cameron, between 2240hrs and 2313hrs. During that time, the players were seen passing chips a total of 12 times after the flop occurred. At 2313hrs, TGS Corey Callaghan issued a warning, after which the players were no longer observed passing any chips. CSM Blair Cameron was present in the surveillance room during the review and identified the guest at spot 9 as Jeff Brooks. CSM Blair Cameron was informed of the findings, and footage was saved as RM202645. Both guests were later removed, picture saved as UM31Jan26(1) and Brooks, Jeff.

Requested Review: Casino Shift Manager Trevor Poole requested a review of the last spin on RL1. Trevor advised that the player wearing black toque was reportedly trying to remove his losing bet from Black when 19R hit. Trevor wished to watch the footage of the incident. Upon review, Surveillance observed the player in question appeared to touch his losing bet at 0131hrs, but he did not move it or remove it from the layout. Trevor attended the Surveillance room to view footage of the incident. Nothing further was required at this time.

PPA Served: Security Relief Supervisor Dante Whiteway advised that PPA #2026009 was currently playing in Zone 3 and that a removal would be initiated. Supervisor Whiteway, along with Security Officers Ashishdeep Singh and Robin Pamma, approached the male for removal. The male was escorted out through Post 2 without incident. Security Relief Supervisor Dante Whiteway later advised that the male was served the PPA, as he was unaware of it during the previous encounter. IR IN20260000220 Created.

Requested Review: CSM Trevor Poole requested a review involving guest Vishal Valand on UTH2 Spot 4, after Dealer Katie Houlihan advised that the guest might have wagered 2x the Ante on the Play after the river (when it should have been 1x the Ante). Upon review, Surveillance observed the incident in question at 0043hrs when the guest appears to wager 2x the Ante on his play bet for $50 ($25 Ante) on the river. The guest won that round. Surveillance, initiated a review of his entire play session when he first arrived on the table at 2338hrs and observed all procedures to be followed with no other instances to note. Live coverage was maintained on the guest until he left the Table at 0130hrs. At no other point was the guest observed not following procedures or attempting to cheat. As a result of it being an isolated occurrence and it did not appear that he was attempting to conceal (he was observed placing his wagers the same way before and after the incident) Surveillance deemed it as an Irregularity. It did not appear that his betting over the limit was intentional, CSM Poole was advised. Footage of the incident dubbed to TG2026-15. IR IN20260000222 was created.
